{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4c263696-0cbf-4026-ba41-eb826211a28a","content":"No worries — here's how to configure it. Create `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- **`command`/`args`** — uses `dotnet run` to build and launch your project.\n- Your MCP server must read JSON-RPC messages from stdin and write responses to stdout (avoid writing logs to stdout — use stderr instead).\n\nIf you've already published the server as a standalone binary, replace the command:\n\n```json\n\"command\": \"src/MyMcpServer/bin/Release/net8.0/MyMcpServer\"\n```\n\nAfter saving, open the Copilot chat panel in agent mode — it will auto-discover the server and list its tools.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4e48bf17-8974-4a20-a1da-f5ee71b0d186","outputTokens":271,"requestId":"AC05:3C3624:E2DD9F:118EE0D:6A012D4B"},"id":"a47a7a09-aa70-4beb-bbc8-9ec3d2cb8bf9","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:13:58.818Z","parentId":"2587acd3-8447-4390-8020-284e17adff97"}
